EXTRACTED VALUE: Deep down, Jericho clearly has the right idea. However, the implementation - which feels half-hearted at times - really lets it down.
I remain a firm supporter of the original PS2 Roses, but this flaccid follow-up fails to get me in the mood. [May 2006, p.89]
Only recommended to those who are completely devoted to F.E.A.R. and who possess a great capability for enduring tedious moments.
